<task id="AUTHV2-048" project="Spaarke Auth v2 + Hardening">
  <metadata>
    <title>Implement audit logging middleware — standard identity fields</title>
    <phase>C — Server hardening</phase>
    <tags>auth, server, observability, audit, FULL</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>C-Parallel-2</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>Add middleware that enriches every authenticated request with standardized identity fields into the structured log scope: oid (Azure AD object ID), appid (calling app), obo flag (true if OBO flow active), tenantId, correlationId. Customer pipes structured logs to their Sentinel/Log Analytics via Diagnostic Settings — uniform fields make their integration mechanical.</prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET engineer with logging + identity expertise.</role>
  <goal>Every authenticated request emits structured log entries with the 5 standard fields. Customer can pipe to their SIEM without per-customer engineering.</goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs (middleware pipeline)</file>
      <file>.claude/AUDIT-FINDINGS-AUTH-SYSTEM.md §3 H-? (claims hardening), §4.1 #5 (audit middleware)</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Create AuditEnrichmentMiddleware in src/Infrastructure/Logging/. Reads HttpContext.User claims: oid, appid (or azp), and detects OBO via amr/scp.</step>
    <step>Use ILogger.BeginScope with dictionary of all 5 fields. Subsequent logs within the request automatically include them.</step>
    <step>Wire in Program.cs after authentication middleware (so claims are available) and before endpoint routing.</step>
    <step>Test: hit an endpoint, inspect App Insights traces. Each trace should have oid, appid, obo, tenantId, correlationId properties.</step>
    <step>Document the field semantics in a README or pattern note.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>AuditEnrichmentMiddleware exists and is wired into Program.cs.</criterion>
    <criterion>App Insights traces show all 5 fields on authenticated requests.</criterion>
    <criterion>OBO detection works (test with an endpoint that exchanges OBO).</criterion>
    <criterion>Field semantics documented.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
